evals.prompt:
I'm designing a response schema for a code-review LLM (Claude Sonnet 4.6 with adaptive thinking enabled). My current draft is:

  {
    "analysis": "<200-500 word string of what the code does>",
    "suggestions": "<200-500 word string of what to change>",
    "severity": "low|medium|high",
    "final_decision": {
      "action": "approve|request_changes|comment",
      "confidence": 0.0-1.0
    }
  }

Is this a good schema? What would you change?
